      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was looking at this part of our transaction processing module and noticed the memory usage is getting higher every time the loop runs. i think it might be something with how we are handling the pointers but i can't spot the exact line. can you take a look at this snippet and tell me why it's leaking?\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_transactions(Transaction* incoming) {\n    for (int i = 0; i < incoming->count; ++i) {\n        Transaction* current = new Transaction(incoming->data[i]);\n        \n        // perform some complex logic\n        apply_interest(current);\n        verify_checksum(current);\n        \n        save_to_ledger(current);\n        // we need to keep track of these for a bit\n        active_transactions.push_back(current);\n    }\n}\n```",
      "source": "evaluator",
